    {
        "content": "<p>What is the proper way to pattern match a <code>Lex (a × b)</code> typed paramter to obtain the left and right element? While <code>intro ⟨l, r⟩</code> got accepted, it creates various type problem down the road (for example, after some substitution I got <code>ofLex (l, r)</code> which is not really correct and simp gets stuck there.</p>",
        "id": 523393873,
        "sender_full_name": "Weiyi Wang",
        "timestamp": 1749603150
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Right now the workaround I have is like</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">intro</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\">-- of type Lex (a × b)</span>\n<span class=\"n\">nth_rw</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"bp\">←</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">toLex_ofLex</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"o\">]</span>\n<span class=\"n\">nth_rw</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"bp\">←</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">toLex_ofLex</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\">-- carefully rewrite each appearance of x</span>\n<span class=\"n\">generalize</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ofLex</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span>\n<span class=\"k\">obtain</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">⟨</span><span class=\"n\">l</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">r</span><span class=\"bp\">⟩</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span>\n<span class=\"c1\">-- now the goal is good to prove</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 523394589,
        "sender_full_name": "Weiyi Wang",
        "timestamp": 1749603746
    },
